'''圣诞空投行动'''（{{lang-en|Operation Christmas Drop}}）是[[美国空军|美国空军]]在1952年开始的一项训练任务。这是[[美国国防部|美国国防部]]全面执行任务时间最长的一次，也是世界上持续时间最长的人道主义空运行动。在[[关岛|关岛]]当地社区的支持下，它主要在[[安德森空军基地|安德森空军基地]]和[[横田空军基地|横田空军基地]]进行，目标是密克罗尼西亚。

==历史==
该行动首次于1951年进行。<ref name=airforce2006/>当时，被分配到第54气象侦察中队（以前被分配到关岛安德森空军基地）的一架WB-29飞机的机组人员正在关岛南部卡平阿马兰吉的密克罗尼西亚环礁上空执行任务。当他们看到岛民向他们挥手时，机组人员迅速收集了一些他们在飞机上的物品，把它们放在一个带有降落伞的集装箱里面，并在他们再次盘旋时放下了货物。<ref>{{cite news|last=Leslie|first=Carlin|title=Operation Christmas Drop, cheer from above|url=http://www.pacaf.af.mil/news/story.asp?id=123283451|accessdate=17 December 2011|website=Pacific Air Forces|date=13 December 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120604101611/http://www.pacaf.af.mil/news/story.asp?id=123283451|archive-date=2012-06-04|dead-url=yes}}</ref> 

目击者说:“我们看到这些东西从飞机后部飞了出来，我大喊:‘有玩具掉下来了’。”<ref name=residentrecalls>{{cite news|last=Robson|first=Seth|title=Yokota resident recalls memories of Operation Christmas Drop|url=http://www.stripes.com/news/yokota-resident-recalls-memories-of-operation-christmas-drop-1.163013|accessdate=17 December 2011|website=Stars and Stripes|date=9 December 2011|archive-date=2019-02-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190207072527/https://www.stripes.com/news/yokota-resident-recalls-memories-of-operation-christmas-drop-1.163013|dead-url=no}}</ref>当时，岛上没有电，也没有自来水，岛上不时受到台风的袭击。最初的一些集装箱未能到达预定地点，岛上居民游出去捡回了一些，而其他一些集装箱几个月后在几英里外被发现。<ref name=residentrecalls/>

今天，这一独特的圣诞节传统在关岛居民和企业的捐赠下得以延续。<ref name=anderson2007/>从C-130飞机上扔下的每个箱子重近400磅（180公斤），里面包括渔网、建筑材料、奶粉、罐头食品、大米、冷却器、衣服、鞋子、玩具和学习用品等物品。<ref name=airforce2006/> 

这是目前仍在全面运作的最古老的国防部任务，<ref name=washpost2011>{{cite news|title=US troops conduct 'Operation Christmas Drop' with care packages raining down on Micronesia|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/asia-pacific/us-troops-conduct-operation-christmas-drop-with-care-packages-raining-down-on-micronesia/2011/12/16/gIQAvFPWxO_story.html|accessdate=17 December 2011|newspaper=Washington Post|date=16 December 2011|archive-date=2019-02-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190207015624/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/asia-pacific/us-troops-conduct-operation-christmas-drop-with-care-packages-raining-down-on-micronesia/2011/12/16/gIQAvFPWxO_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>也是世界上运行时间最长的人道主义空运。<ref name=anderson2007>{{cite news|last=Morgan|first=Clarissa|title=Operation Christmas Drop delivers supplies to Pacific islands|url=http://www.andersen.af.mil/news/story.asp?id=123071202|accessdate=17 December 2011|website=Anderson Air Force Base|date=10 October 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071024200747/http://www.andersen.af.mil/news/story.asp?id=123071202|archive-date=2007-10-24|dead-url=yes}}</ref>到2006年，运送的物资超过80万磅（36万公斤）。<ref name=airforce2006/>这次行动给部队提供了进行人道主义空投的机会，因为部队将在部署后在伊拉克或阿富汗进行空投。<ref name=residentrecalls/>

来自安徒生空军基地的志愿者，包括734空军机动性中队，以及日本横田空军基地第36空运中队的机组人员和飞机参加了此次行动。关岛社区的成员也帮助这项行动。<ref name=airforce2006>{{cite news|last=Griffin|first=J.D.|title=Volunteers complete annual Operation Christmas Drop|url=http://www.af.mil/news/story.asp?storyID=123036009|accessdate=17 December 2011|website=U.S. Air Force|date=21 December 2006|archive-url=https://archive.is/20121212030538/http://www.af.mil/news/story.asp?storyID=123036009|archive-date=2012-12-12|dead-url=no}}</ref>运营资金是通过赞助活动筹集的，如高尔夫比赛和赞助跑步，以及当地企业赞助单个盒子。<ref name=airforce2006/>

在2006年的行动中，140个箱子落到了59个岛屿上。<ref name=airforce2006/>2011年的行动包括向[[法斯岛|法斯岛]]投放25箱静脉输液，以防治当地爆发的[[登革热|登革热]]。<ref name=washpost2011/>这些集装箱被扔进离海滩不远的水中，以避免击中任何当地人。<ref name=residentrecalls/>

2014年，太平洋空军向56个密克罗尼西亚岛屿运送了5万磅物资。<ref>{{cite av media|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u0G6XKBrrJM|title=Operation Christmas Drop 2014|date=14 January 2015|publisher=Yokota Air Base|accessdate=8 February 2016|via=YouTube|archive-date=2020-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200623092838/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=u0G6XKBrrJM|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2015年，[[日本航空自卫队|日本航空自卫队]]和[[澳大利亚皇家空军|澳大利亚皇家空军]]与美国空军一起参与了行动。日本和澳大利亚各提供了一架C-130大力神运输机，加入美国提供的三架C-130运输机的行列。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2015/12/14/national/aussies-japan-join-u-s-air-force-pacific-island-christmas-food-toy-drop-started-1952/#.Vm7ezEqDFBc|title=Australia, Japan join U.S. Air Force in Pacific island Christmas food, toy drop that started in 1952|work=The Japan Times|accessdate=8 February 2016|archive-date=2019-04-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190425060631/https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2015/12/14/national/aussies-japan-join-u-s-air-force-pacific-island-christmas-food-toy-drop-started-1952/#.Vm7ezEqDFBc|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Australia, Japan join U.S. Air Force in Pacific island Christmas food, toy drop that started in 1952 |url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2015/12/14/national/aussies-japan-join-u-s-air-force-pacific-island-christmas-food-toy-drop-started-1952/#.WhAuJ0tx2CR |work=[[Japan_Times|Japan Times]] |date=December 14, 2015 |access-date=November 18, 2017 |archive-date=2019-04-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190425060631/https://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2015/12/14/national/aussies-japan-join-u-s-air-force-pacific-island-christmas-food-toy-drop-started-1952/#.WhAuJ0tx2CR |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.yokota.af.mil/News/Article-Display/Article/773845/operation-christmas-drop-showcases-hadr-training/ |title=Operation Christmas Drop showcases HA/DR Training |last=Mekpongsatorn |first=Melissa K. |date=December 17, 2015 |website=Yokota Air Base |access-date=November 18, 2017 |archive-date=2020-09-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200917190329/https://www.yokota.af.mil/News/Article-Display/Article/773845/operation-christmas-drop-showcases-hadr-training/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.airliftmagazine.com/ocd2015/ |title=Operation Christmas Drop showcases HA/DR Training |date=December 2015 |website=Airlift Magazine |access-date=November 18, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201030429/http://www.airliftmagazine.com/ocd2015/ |archive-date=2017-12-01 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=The 2015 Operation Christmas Drop |date=December 2015 |url=http://www.micronesia.emb-japan.go.jp/nikokukan/The%202015%20Operation%20Christmas%20Drop.pdf |website=micronesia.emb-japan.go.jp |access-date=November 18, 2017 |archive-date=2020-09-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200917185817/https://www.micronesia.emb-japan.go.jp/nikokukan/The%202015%20Operation%20Christmas%20Drop.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite av media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zzQ0jL5R09k |title=Japan Air Self-Defense Force of Operation Christmas Drop |date=December 18, 2015 |publisher=US Military Channel |access-date=November 18, 2017 |via=YouTube |archive-date=2020-11-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201106170050/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zzQ0jL5R09k |dead-url=no }}</ref>日本航空自卫队和澳大利亚皇家空军也参与了2016年<ref>{{cite web |title=Operation Christmas Drop: Behind the Scenes |url=http://www.dla.mil/AboutDLA/News/NewsArticleView/Article/1028004/operation-christmas-drop-behind-the-scenes |last=Presentado |first=Cierra |date=December 12, 2016 |website=Defense Logistic Agency |access-date=November 19, 2017 |archive-date=2018-08-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180829063046/http://www.dla.mil/AboutDLA/News/NewsArticleView/Article/1028004/operation-christmas-drop-behind-the-scenes/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>和2017年的作战。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navy.mil/submit/display.asp?story_id=103734 |title=Operation Christmas Drop 2017 in Full Flight |last=Mediola |first=Tanya |date=December 12, 2017 |website=Official Website of the United States Navy |accessdate=2020-12-29 |archive-date=2018-07-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180729000245/http://www.navy.mil/submit/display.asp?story_id=103734 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite